# unmappedSfSymbolsName

**Instance Property**

The element’s system symbol, not the remapped symbol.

## Declaration

```swift
var unmappedSfSymbolsName: String? { get set }
```

## Discussion

Use this property to get the original unmapped name. Otherwise, use the [doc://com.apple.gamecontroller/documentation/GameController/GCControllerElement/sfSymbolsName] property to get the possibly remapped symbol.

## Displaying a symbol

- **sfSymbolsName**: A system symbol for the element or the remapped element.
